				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Essentially using RAM is simple (no need to bank 8KB of CHR-RAM), cost-effective, and flexible.  Using ROM is speedy and good when you are approaching the board's PRG-ROM limit.  
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The later Megaman games uses the MMC3's capability to switch multiple parts of the sprite tileset individually to swap in new enemies and animations mid-level. </div>
<br />
<br />Only Mega Man 3 and 5 do this, as they use CHR-ROM.  Mega Man 4 and 6 use CHR-RAM, so they would have to rely on other methods to swap sprite tiles in mid-level.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

